scientists complete the sequence of chromosaic chromosome , which has a bearing on the initial loss of intellectual disease .
( agence france - presse , paris , 2 nd ) - a group of international scientists said that they have completed the sequence of the 14 th pair of human chromosaic chromosaic , which is related to many diseases , including the initial stage of alzheimer 's disease that is likely to be suffering from over 30 years of age .
this is the fourth pair of chromosaic chromosaic , which is composed of more than 87 million pairs of non - oxygen dna ( dol ) .
the study published by the british natural science weekly showed that the 14 th pair of chromosome were made up of 1,050 genetic and genetic segments .
the goal of genetic scientists is to provide diagnosis tools to discover defects and eventually provide treatment that can prevent these genes from creating obstacles .
the international scientists , led by the french gene research center , gomez , said that the 14 th pairs of chromosaic genes and more than 60 diseases genes that have a bearing on the immunity system .
in previous studies on many diseases , 14 pairs of chromosome have been identified , including a type of cryptosis , perforation , certain types of vision and hearing damage , and initial alzheimer 's disease .
about 200,000 people in the united states are suffering from initial alzheimer 's disease , accounting for five percent of the total number of people suffering from the disease .
mankind has 23 pairs of chromosome .
in the past three years , three pairs of chromosome have been completed , including 20 pairs , 21 pairs and 22 pairs .
