canada , like the european union and australia , closed their embassies on november 28 and reopened earlier this week .
hubble said that all the three ambassadors were satisfied with the security measures taken by the philippine government .
the closure of the embassy has irritated the philippine government , saying that the so - called threat is too exaggerated and the closure of the embassy has hurt the image of the philippines .
manila has dismissed police intelligence officials as he disclosed unconfirmed intelligence about the terrorist threats to the australian and canadian embassies .
the eu office and the australian embassy were in the same building .
around the anniversary of the september 11 terrorist attacks in the united states , western diplomatic envoys in southeast asia closed down one after another because they were threatened by the al - qaeda group and its local alliance .
australian fm says north korea 's bad behavior will not be able to get more aid
( agence france - presse , sydney , 2 nd ) - australia has called on the international community to work together to make north korea believe that contempt for the nuclear nonproliferation agreement or other " bad behavior " will not be able to obtain more aid or other concessions .
australian foreign minister downer said today that pyongyang 's decision to reactivate a controversial nuclear facility and expel un monitoring personnel is obviously aimed at forcing the international community to make concessions in aid and trade .
australia is one of the few countries with diplomatic relations with north korea .
downer said : " we think what north korea wants to do is to go against the framework of the 1994 agreement and to obtain concessions , aid , and trade from other countries in the world , including the united states . "
downer said in an interview with the australian broadcasting corporation , " one of the important points we have put forward to north korea is that bad behavior will not be rewarded . "
downer pointed out , " the expulsion of un monitoring personnel and the reactivate of the yongbyon nuclear facilities will stop the international community from providing support . "
" this will produce an adverse effect , and we hope these diplomatic measures will be effective . "
" on the other hand , if we react too much , it will be the case of north korea .
we do n't want to do that . "
downer said australia is working closely with the united states and other major allies to force north korea to withdraw its recent steps to resume a frozen nuclear program .
downer said : " what we want to do is to ensure that the international community will jointly adopt countermeasures , and we do not want to adopt uncoordinated special countermeasures . "
