( agence france - presse , los angeles ) - prosecutors said that a former head of the us online real estate company , " housing shop " , had agreed to settle the charges of fraud and the lawsuit against the insider dealing scandal .
the former senior manager of the housing shop , kariana , has agreed to plead guilty to one count of securities fraud involving inside transactions , a special assistant to the us investigation officer said .
another prosecutor , fox , said that kariana also agreed to pay 70,000 us dollars to settle a civil lawsuit with the us stock exchange against him .
winnie said that the maximum penalty for securities fraud is 10 years ' imprisonment , but it is expected that the above sentence will be " significantly shortened " according to the agreement of admitting the crime .
prosecutors and investigators pointed out that in the financial fraud plot involving qana , the chief executive of the housing shops used the report on revenue in 2001 to mislead investors .
fox said that karana knew that after the stock market was filled with water , he had taken off the shares of his own housing shop , and " wall street did not notice that the key revenue of the housing shop was false . "
the former vice - president of the housing shop , tai simo , who was charged with a similar offence of insider dealing , has pleaded guilty and the court is scheduled to announce the verdict on april 21 .
the chief operating officer of the housing shop , mr jizzek and the former financial secretary , mr joseph prueher , pleaded guilty to charges of securities fraud .
the prosecutor said that the company 's chief executives , jizzek and joseph prueher , were suspected to have been involved in the accounting of housing shops , and the amount of revenue had been filled up .
