( agence france - presse , vienna , 8 th ) - heavy snow in the past few days , low temperatures in siberia , and strong winds in various parts of europe have caused many deaths . at the same time , highway , railway , air , and sea traffic have been suspended .
last night , the temperature in the russian capital of moscow dropped to a level that even local people felt cold , killing six people , bringing the number of people who died from the cold to 239 this year , most of whom were homeless and elderly people , including many of them .
three people died in lithuania last night , and many people had to cut their legs and fingers due to frozen injuries .
in the southern part of the country , the temperature dropped to a new low of minus 32.6 degrees celsius in 16 years .
on monday , three indian illegal immigrants died of cold and fatigue in slovakia , with local temperatures falling to minus 20 degrees celsius .
at the same time , the civil defense units in various parts of europe and other regions have indicated that the snowfall has caused road closure , train delays , and airport paralysis .
traffic in some areas has been paralyzed by ice and road accidents along the british railway , with heavy snow falling in the eastern part of the country .
in the czech republic , which was hit by serious flooding last summer , the temperature in the border areas near slovakia was low to minus 18 degrees celsius .
world research center lauds environmental revolution
( agence france - presse , washington , 9 th ) - in its annual report on the " current world situation " , the world 's environmental research center , the environmental research organization , praised the arrival of the " environmental revolution " with an unusual optimistic attitude , pointing out that many countries are successfully curbing and resolving environmental , health , and social problems .
" the person in charge of the world research center , fleischer , said on the 9 th : " establishing a world that meets our needs , and at the same time allowing the next generation to enjoy a healthy society , is no longer a dream of the white day . "
the current world situation report points out that one of the encouraging achievements is the use of renewable energy sources in germany , japan and spain , such as solar energy and wind vehicles , which are becoming more and more common .
" we are entering a new era , " fleischer said when talking about the success of the strategy of rebirth energy .
the report said that in the 1990 s , the global production of fluorine - free hydrocarbon -- the destruction of the ozone layer -- decreased by 81 percent .
in addition , the world health organization 's campaign against polio has reduced the number of cases of polio from 350,000 in 1988 to 480 in 2001 .
the washington - based environmental research organization also praised the local environmental achievements , for example , the netherlands has created 86 percent of the car recovery rate , denmark has completely banned the use of aluminum cans to convert the recovered glass bottles , and brazil started to use renewable energy in 2001 .
the organization 's report said that past achievements have brought hope to lift the serious global threat , including malaria , which has claimed 7,000 lives per day , and air , food and water pollution that has caused the unfortunate death of 5,500 children every day .
