( agence france - presse , washington , 12th ) - aol time warner chairman kerry announced tonight that he will resign in may . he said , " this is the best for the company . "
explaining his decision , kiss said that he had decided to take steps to avoid shareholders ' criticism of him , which " has hindered our ability to cooperate like a team , and has placed the focus on our business . "
kerry , who monitors the merger between aol and time warner , which was agreed by the us federal council in january 2001 , will still be the director of aol and aol time warner board .
the merger , which was announced in january 2000 , valued at $ 155 billion , was approved by european policymakers later that year .
" as you have expected , this decision is very difficult for me personally . as i hope to be the chairman of this big company in the next few years , and as a co - author of the case , i have always believed that it is very important for me to leave the board of directors and help the matter on the track , " he said in a statement .
he stressed : " first of all , there is no need for the company to be uneasy at this critical moment , and because some shareholders are still gathering their disappointment at the operation after the merger of the company on me , i have decided that we should take action now to prevent our cooperation like a team from being hindered and put the focus on our business . "
aol time warner said that it expects its advertising and business sales in 2002 to drop from 2.7 billion us dollars in 2001 to 1.5 billion to 1.6 billion us dollars .
the total sales volume will be $ 8.8 billion to $ 9 billion , compared with $ 8.718 billion in the previous year .
the company estimated that the total sales volume of us online in 2003 was almost the same as that of 2002 , and that advertising and business sales would be reduced by 40 to 50 percent .
north korea to withdraw from nuclear non - proliferation treaty
( agence france - presse , washington , 15 th ) - u . s . and north korea have upgraded their stalls from the " axis of evil " to an international crisis , and the efforts of global nuclear non - proliferation over the past decades may be just one step short of success .
pyongyang announced its withdrawal from the nuclear non - proliferation treaty ( npt ) on the 10 th of this month , dropping a confrontation with washington .
analysts said that the world 's efforts to curb the proliferation of nuclear weapons are likely to fail , and the treaty has been seriously damaged when the non - signatory states india and pakistan entered the nuclear club in 1998 .
four days after pyongyang took the above action , the five permanent members of the un security council took preventive diplomatic action against the crisis .
russia said it would send a special envoy to pyongyang to propose an end to the deadlock , while china suggested a compromise dialogue between the united states and north korea .
britain and france discussed the crisis in london .
the international atomic energy agency has warned that if pyongyang refuses to give up its nuclear program , it may ask the security council to take action .
with regard to the actions of russia and china , many us observers believe that such talks may force moscow and beijing to decide whether to vote against north korea .
other countries with nuclear capabilities , such as iran and libya , will certainly keep a close watch on the development of the north korean crisis .
they will pay attention to north korea 's withdrawal from the nuclear non - proliferation treaty and will not be punished , or will obtain huge us funds in exchange for stopping the development of nuclear weapons .
" if north korea is considered to have the ability to withdraw from the nuclear non - proliferation treaty , they may be calculated , and they can take the same action without paying the price , " said the former state department arms control official ai enhong .
the international economic research institute believes that north korea may have made a tactical mistake because the decision to withdraw from the nuclear non - proliferation treaty will make the international community more determined to resolve this issue .
japanese court rejects huge compensation for former chinese slaves
( agence france - presse , tokyo , 15 th ) - a japanese court today rejected a compensation lawsuit of 132 - million yen ( 1.1 - million us dollars ) , which was initiated by six chinese people who were forced to work as slaves at a nickel mine in japan during world war ii .
a judge of the kyoto district court said that although the government and the japanese metallurgical industry company had committed a common illegal act in 1944 , he rejected the lawsuit on the basis of the civil law for 20 years .
nannan said : " the defendant 's responsibility has been terminated . "
the five former chinese slaves , including the 72 - year - old liu zonggen and a lackey , sought unpaid wages , compensation , and apology from the japanese government and the japanese metallurgical industry company .
these six had worked as slaves for one year in japan 's metallurgical industry . during this period , they were often beaten , and they were unable to eat and wear enough .
the japanese metallurgical industry argued that the company was unable to confront the state 's policy , while the japanese government said that according to the constitution at that time , it did not need to pay compensation to the plaintiff .
jiji news agency reported that after the court announced the verdict , liu zonggen said at a press conference : " this is a humanitarian judgment . "
he said they would appeal .
liu zonggen said , " i have won the support of many japanese friends , and i will fight to the end . "
the plaintiff 's lawyer pointed out that the ruling " violated the historical record " and demanded that the japanese government and the japanese metallurgical industry pay compensation and apologize to resolve this problem .
the defence was rejected for the first time in the war compensation litigation , kyodo news reported .
in 1944 , the japanese army arrested about 200 chinese , and then sent them to the dayton nickel mine in the city of calgary as slaves .
