japan is expected to reach 1.5 percent growth in real terms in 2006
( agence france - presse , tokyo ) - japan 's economic and financial news reported today that the japanese government 's economic and financial advisory conference has extended the forecast for japan 's economy to grow by more than 1.5 percent in real terms for two years to 2006 .
the economic and financial advisory conference also expected that the total annual issuance of treasury bonds in the next five years would be as high as 40 trillion yen , as the reduction of the budget deficit would be longer than expected .
the report said that the mid - term economic outlook report , which aims to stimulate the economic and financial operation guidelines for the next five years , is scheduled to be finalized on the 20 th of this month .
the mid - term economic outlook report was originally planned in early january last year , and the economic and financial advisory conference is now being revised and is expected to be approved by the cabinet by the end of this month .
the report said that the current edition of the medium - term economic outlook report and a trial of the cabinet government are expected to reach 1.5 percent in real terms in 2004 and 2.7 percent in 2005 .
however , the revised version is expected to grow by only 0.9 percent in real terms in 2004 and 0.8 percentage points in nominal terms .
the revised version is expected to reach 1.5 percent or more in real terms in the 2006 fiscal year , the report said .
it is necessary to see a growth rate of 2.5 percent or more in the fiscal year 2007 , which is two years later than the original estimate .
the report pointed out that the revised outlook report will also extend the timetable for extricating the country from deflation for two years .
