( agence france - presse , sydney , 18 th ) - the fire in australia has destroyed nearly 40 houses today and threatened residents in the suburbs of the capital of canberra . with strong winds and rising temperatures , the fire is expected to further expand .
australian officials said that unconfirmed reports pointed out that the fire in dozens of villages and towns around canberra and other areas of the australian capital city 's direct jurisdiction , which had caused one death and several missing .
federal police officer brown said police were trying to confirm that at least one person was killed in the fire , but it was true that some people were missing .
because of strong winds , the forest fire in the northern , southern , and western mountainous areas of canberra was out of control , the authorities of the capital 's direct jurisdiction announced today that the whole region was in an emergency state .
on the other hand , the fire authorities said that since the fire was approaching the densely populated area , the military had been called in to join the several thousand firefighters who put out the fire .
under the threat of the most serious forest fire in the past 50 years , people in the mountainous areas of the national park of new south wales , the snow - capped mountains in the province of new south wales and the kayzko , have been urgently evacuated .
" the situation is very grim , and the snow - capped mountains may be facing the most serious threat in 50 years , " said the director of the village fire services department , kepeiberg , who said , adding that more than 1,000 firefighters are fighting a battle of continuous defeat and are unable to stop the fire from eroding the 80,000 hectares of forest land in the new south wales province .
