( agence france - presse , tokyo , 18 th ) - japanese emperor akihito received an operation today to get rid of cancer . doctors of the royal family said that the operation was smooth and the cancer cells seemed to have not spread to other organs .
" the operation has been carried out smoothly as scheduled and has been successfully completed , " he said at a press conference held at the tokyo university hospital .
your majesty has been awakened by narcotic drugs and has talked with the princess who accompanied him . "
he added : " judging from the appearance , we believe that ( cancer ) has not spread . "
he said further tests would be conducted by doctors to ascertain that cancer is limited to the uterus .
the operation was jointly carried out by six doctors , which took three hours and 40 minutes to remove the entire surrogacy of akihito .
the 69 - year - old akihito was in a position in 1989 . this is the first time that the emperor of japan has received an operation in a hospital outside the imperial hospital .
doctors said akihito is scheduled to stay on for about a month .
jinze said that during the operation , akihito did not have much bleeding , and doctors only used his own blood for blood transfusion .
prior to this operation , doctors had stored the blood of akihito in advance , and the number of such blood was unknown .
chief cabinet secretary yasuo fukuda said that the government was pleased with the success of the japanese emperor 's operation and hoped that he would recover at an early date .
government officials said that before akihito was admitted to hospital , the 42 - year - old crown prince deren had temporarily taken over the constitutional duties of the emperor .
this is the first time that the emperor has been transferred to the hospital due to illness .
