( agence france - presse , manila , 20 th ) - philippine security forces are gathering forces to fight a large number of attacks by communist guerrillas in some areas of the southeast asian archipelago .
brigade commander prueher said today that the new people 's army is " attempting to gather troops in certain areas , " including the northern philippines , the southern provinces of manila , and a number of central islands .
he added : " they have stepped up attacks on some areas that they think are weak in military strength , " or " attacked and disturbed troops in a small area of smoke . "
other officials said that the new people 's army has stepped up attacks on so - called " soft " targets , such as telecommunications and power facilities .
last week , the head of the state police , aibudan , asked the telecommunications company to invest several hundred million us dollars in security to prevent attacks by the new people 's army .
prueher said , " the armed forces have re - deployed more troops in areas most likely to be threatened . "
joseph prueher said that the number of staff of the new people 's army had decreased by at least 23 percent from 12,000 to 13,000 two years ago to about 9,000 .
among them , at least 5,000 are " regular armed forces " and about 6,000 in early 2001 .
he said that the government troops had repelled them in more than 400 villages where the new people 's army often appeared .
he said : " we are slowly but definitely winning the people 's confidence . "
last week , the new people 's army suffered a serious military and political setback and forced it to return to the negotiating table with the philippine communist party at its source , the national security adviser said .
after the rebels assassinated two philippine congressmen , philippine president arroyo stopped negotiations with the communist party in mid - 2001 .
last year , the united states listed the new people 's army and the philippine communist party as its " foreign terrorist organization " international blacklist .
washington , canada and many western european governments also agreed to trace and stop the rebels ' foreign financial sources and freeze their overseas assets .
china 's cell phone users will slow down
( agence france - presse , beijing , 21st ) - the number of new mobile phone users in mainland china is expected to be reduced to 52 million this year .
last year , the figure was 61.9 million .
however , the beijing post today quoted a forecast by the ministry of information industry as saying that this goal might be underestimated .
in january last year , the ministry of information industry predicted that the number of new mobile phone users in that year was 55 million , but the actual figure was 61.9 million .
at the end of last year , there were 206.6 million mobile phone users in mainland china , up 42.7 percent from the previous year .
beijing said that in july last year , mainland china became the world 's largest fixed network and mobile phone market .
one year ago , cell phone users alone ranked first in the world .
at the same time , information industry minister wu jichuan predicted that the decline in fixed assets investment in the post industry will be suspended this year , but the investment may be the same , the report said .
last year , investment in fixed assets in the post industry decreased by 20 percent to 2210.6 billion yuan .
the telecommunications industry accounts for 97 percent of the total investment .
wu jichuan predicted that this year , the investment in fixed assets of the post industry will reach 210 billion yuan , slightly lower than last year .
the ministry of information industry estimates that the number of new fixed - line telephone users this year is 33 million , lower than last year 's 35.4 million , the report said .
at the end of december last year , the number of fixed - line telephone users on the chinese mainland reached 241.4 million , an increase of 35 million over the previous year .
wu jichuan also promised to strengthen competition and speed up the establishment of a telecommunications control organization .
he said : " the optimization of telecommunications control has become the most important issue in the telecommunications industry .
we will speed up the drafting of the telecommunications law and revise the postal , judicial , and wireless management regulations . "
