north korea has no intention to produce nuclear weapons : report
( afp , seoul ) south korean officials said that the north korean delegation to the south - north ministerial meeting said today that north korea has no intention to produce nuclear weapons .
south korean delegation spokesman li fengchao said : " north korea stressed that it has no intention of producing nuclear weapons . "
the north korean delegation made the remarks after south korea urged the pyongyang regime to abandon its nuclear ambitions , in a briefing on the first official talks in an hour .
" the south korean side stressed that if the issue of nuclear weapons is not resolved , the entire south - north korean relations will certainly not be able to continue to move forward , " li fengchao said .
li fengchao added : " we hope that through this round of talks , north korea will be persuaded to take more concrete steps to reverse its decision to reopen its nuclear facilities that can produce weapons - grade plutonium . "
the focus of the south - north ministerial talks is on reconciliation and humanitarian issues , but south korea , a traditional ally of the united states , has said that seoul is determined to use the opportunity of the south - north korean talks to express the international community 's concern over the nuclear deadlock .
north korea claimed that the nuclear stalemate was only a bilateral issue involving the united states , and other countries ' intervention would only complicate the issue .
marriott , the largest chain retailers in the united states , is expected to make early profits
( agence france - presse , michigan , 26th ) - u . s . 's largest chain retail outlet , kaz , said that after a year of restructuring , the company will get out of the bankruptcy predicament in 2004 and return to profit .
the restructuring plan put forward by the company on the day before yesterday mainly relied on the two investment companies - - the one - million richest man in the state of kangnai , and the third largest capital fund company in new york . these two investment companies are preparing to invest us $ 352 - million to save the company .
however , the restructuring plan has not been approved by the lending banks , investors and suppliers .
this chain of retailers with a century - old history said it would continue to communicate with the creditor 's commission and hoped to extricate itself from the predicament of bankruptcy by april 30 .
the us federal bureau of investigation , the securities and exchange commission , and the energy and business committee of the house of representatives are conducting an investigation into kaj . the reason is that high - ranking officials are suspected of being involved in financial fraud .
the board of directors of the company also conducted an internal investigation and said the night before that it had found " reliable and convincing evidence " , indicating that 10 executive officers had violated management responsibility .
kaem announced bankruptcy a year ago after losing us $ 2.4 billion in 2001 .
it estimated a loss of 3.26 billion us dollars in 2002 and said the company would lose 186 million us dollars this year .
kaem has closed 283 stores , and at the same time laid off 22,000 people . at present , it plans to close 300 more stores and lay off 37,000 people .
