( agence france - presse , davos , switzerland , 25th ) - u . s . secretary of state powell said that the u . s . plan to attack iraq has the support of more than 10 allies .
at this time , he is preparing a draft related to us policy for attending the world economic forum .
under tight security measures , powell arrived at the swiss ski resort of davos to deliver a speech at the annual meeting of global political and business leaders on sunday .
at the same time , the anti - globalization protesters also gathered there .
the concern over the war in iraq has cast a shadow over this year 's meeting .
the member states of the organization of petroleum exporting countries ( opec ) today tried to ease their misgivings about the possible suspension of world oil supply once the united states launches an attack on iraq .
powell told reporters who were accompanying the delegation on the visit to davos that " quite a few countries have indicated that they will act in unison with us . " he also said that even if the un security council does not support the war , the attitude of these countries will not change .
powell said : " we will not be alone , and this can be confirmed .
in my memory , i can refer to more than 10 countries . at the same time , i think more countries will express their support . "
us officials said that powell would hold different talks with turkish prime minister chuo and australian prime minister downer during the meeting in davos .
turkey is an important nato ally of the united states , and is now resisting pressure to join the us - led war against iraq .
as for the australian government , it vowed to send troops to participate in the war in disregard of domestic opposition .
