( agence france - presse , washington , 28 th ) - senate democratic leader daschle raised objections to president bush 's proof that iraq possesses weapons of mass destruction . he also questioned whether the white house has a set of " guiding principles " to prove that there is a proper reason to attack saddam .
" if we have the evidence of iraq 's possession of nuclear and biological weapons , why is it not known to the world ? just as president kennedy had a photo of cuba 's possession of offensive missiles 40 years ago , he immediately instructed ambassador to the united nations , the ambassador to the united nations , the united nations , to announce it at the un general assembly . "
at a time when the un arms inspectors reported to the un security council whether iraq would abide by the arms reduction order , daschle fiercely criticized president bush when reporting to the national press club in washington .
he said : " at a time when we are beginning to engage in a war against terrorism , the american people have the right to understand why they want to send thousands of us troops to the battlefield at risk of life , and the united states has to spend billions of us dollars to attack its allies at the expense of its opponents and to provoke attacks on iraq . "
" in a democratic country , it is very important that the president should try his best to defuse the people 's doubts and resolve the people 's misgivings , " said daschle .
