space shuttle disaster may lead to suspension of space operations : russian expert
( agence france - presse , moscow ) - a russian space expert pointed out that the unfortunate incident of the breakup of u . s . space shuttle columbia on its way back to the earth may lead to the temporary suspension of the human mission of the international space station by the u . s . space shuttle and the russian spacecraft .
the russian space expert , who did not want to be named , told the interfax news agency that the accident of the breakup of the colombian spacecraft when it returned to the atmosphere would force the astronauts on the space station to return to the ground and open the automatic system of the space station for a period of time .
he said that if the cause of the accident was confirmed to be caused by the age of the shuttle , the united states would freeze all the missions of the shuttle to prevent the recurrence of similar disasters .
he further pointed out that it is very likely that the united states will send astronauts to the space station until 2007 or 2008 , and will have to build a new spacecraft .
if the us space shuttle stops , russia will only be able to send its astronauts to the space station . however , the russian space agency is facing a serious financial difficulty . therefore , the united states and russia may reach an agreement on the use of the united nations to maintain the human mission of the space station in order to make up for the international space station .
the russian expert said that the astronauts on the international space station were originally scheduled to return to the earth on march 1 , and now they should stay on the space station .
the international space station program includes 16 countries , including the united states , russia , japan , canada , and france .
russian experts pointed out that the unfortunate incident on the 1 st showed that the space shuttle could not be relied on , and that russia was also out of the mind in 1971 , when the joint spacecraft no . 11 crashed when it returned to the earth , resulting in the loss of three astronauts on the spacecraft .
new czech president leaves office yet to be confirmed
( agence france - presse , prague , 2 nd ) - harry , a playwright who became a hero of the democratic movement during the era of the communist party of the czech republic 's rule , today bid farewell to his official life and resigned from his post as the elected president for 13 years .
in his television speech , hadi thanked the people for their trust in him . he said : " if not for your understanding and goodwill , i will not be able to stay in the office for a while . "
despite the serious health problems , he is still under great pressure , and although his successor has not yet been determined , he is still stepping down as scheduled .
hadi was sworn in on december 29 , 1989 . on the same day , he made his first speech to the public on the yangtai station in brundtland . earlier today , he also expressed his best wishes to hundreds of people at the same place . he said : " i will bid farewell to you 13 years after i assumed the presidency . "
this 66 - year - old writer was originally a dissidents , but later he changed to a world - class politician . this also means that democracy has defeated the polar power in europe .
after the revolution in the czech republic , hadi , who was once a prisoner of the communist regime , became president .
three years later , the czech republic was divided into two countries , the czech republic and slovakia , and the czech republic continued to be the president of the czech republic .
the president was handed over to prime minister jean - claude juncker and the speaker of the house of representatives , who are scheduled to take over the presidential power for the time being from tomorrow until the new president is elected .
the czech parliament held a meeting last month to elect a new president , but no results were achieved in the two polls on january 15 and 24 .
