nearly 3,000 us troops stationed in south korea ordered to freeze deployment
( agence france - presse , seoul , 3 rd ) - u . s . military claimed that about 2,900 u . s . generals and soldiers who are scheduled to leave south korea in the next three months have been ordered to freeze their defense , so that the troops can maintain their combat readiness .
the freeze was not directly related to the north korean nuclear crisis , but highlighted the united states ' two - sided efforts to deal with the iraqi and north korean issues .
the eighth us army corps in seoul said today that they had received a freeze order to maintain the scale of us troops stationed in south korea . at the same time when iraq and afghanistan were also carrying out similar military deployment , the replacement plan of us military units in the united states was also suspended .
lieutenant general kang bell , commander of the eighth army group , issued a statement aimed at ensuring the strength of the us troops stationed in south korea .
according to the defense treaty signed between south korea and the united states , there are about 37,000 us troops stationed in south korea , and us troops in south korea have been on alert since north korea 's nuclear ambitions were exposed in december last year .
suspected wreckage of space shuttle found in west california and arizona
( agence france - presse , houston ) - u . s . national aviation and space agency ( nasa ) said that the wreckage of the suspected crash of the columbia space shuttle was also found in california and arizona in the western part of the united states . this or the permission provided important clues to why the space shuttle would break down in the air .
" we have received many reports that we have found the wreckage on the ground of california and arizona , " said kirstnik , deputy director of the state aviation and space agency .
he said that a team of experts had been instructed to inspect the wreckage at various locations in these states , but it was also prudent to point out what was not yet known .
a special task force has been formed by the space agency to search for the wreckage in texas and west carolina , where most of the remains of the shuttle were found , said the space program manager , the space shuttle .
the wreckage is likely to be important because it can provide key parts of the cause of the crash , he said .
on the 1 st , the columbia space shuttle was scheduled to land at 9 : 16 a.m . ( 10 : 16 p.m . taipei time ) in the air before the kennedy space center in florida , and the seven astronauts on the spacecraft were all killed .
investigators are trying to find out why the temperature on the left side of the space shuttle was up to 16 degrees celsius a few minutes before the suspension of communications , and the unusual pulling force on the left side of the space shuttle at the same time caused the shuttle to get out of control .
krajisnik said that the possibility of finding the wreckage in a place more west than originally expected was regarded as important in clarifying the cause of the crash .
he said : " it is of utmost importance to review the wreckage in the early stage of the crash . "
