german unemployment rises to five - year high in january
( agence france - presse , frankfurt , 5 th ) - according to official data , the bad weather and long - term economic slump in winter have pushed the unemployment rate in germany to a new high in january this year , setting a new high in five years , causing german chancellor schroeder , who has just been re - elected for 100 days , to suffer another heavy blow .
in addition , with the threat of a possible war in iraq , germany , the biggest economy in the euro zone , is getting more and more depressed .
the freeze in the german labor market seems to continue in the next few months .
data released by the federal labor department in newcastle , germany , show that the number of people seeking jobs in germany has risen to 4623,000 , or 11.1% of the german labor force , and the unemployment rate in january has reached a new high in five years since march 1988 .
in december last year , the total unemployed population reached 4.225 million , and the unemployment rate was equal to 10.1 percent .
due to seasonal factors , the unemployment population in germany is usually on the rise in winter , with the general companies , especially the construction industry , being dismissed due to bad weather .
however , even if this reason is taken into account , the number of people who applied for unemployment relief last month continued to increase .
the total number of unemployed people in january rose from 4212,000 in december last year to 4274,000 , according to the latest seasonally adjusted data released by the frankfurt central bank .
meanwhile , the seasonally adjusted unemployment rate increased from 10.1% to 10.3% .
director of the federal labor bureau , gester , will be attributed to the extraordinary winter weather and economic difficulties .
singapore 's economy expected to recover in 2004 : report
( agence france - presse , singapore , 6 th ) - singapore 's economic review committee said that due to global geopolitical and economic tension , singapore 's economy is expected to recover in full by 2004 .
the singapore economic review committee said in its annual report : " singapore 's economy has yet to completely recover from the recession since 2001 . there are too many instability in the region , the slowdown in the economies of europe , the united states , and japan , the imminent trigger of the iraq war , and the major challenges of the chinese mainland have cast a shadow on singapore 's recent economic prospects . "
however , there is still a reasonable opportunity for singapore 's economy to grow this year , but it may have to wait until 2004 for a full recovery .
singapore 's economy is expected to grow by 2 to 5 percent this year after a 2.2 percent economic growth last year , but is still far lower than singapore 's annual growth rate of 7.3 percent since 1985 .
the economic audit commission also suggested that the government should extend the plan to restore the rate of the employers ' provident fund payment . two years later , it will consider raising the rate of the employers ' provident fund payment , so as to avoid increasing the burden on employers in the current difficult period , help reduce the unemployment rate , and send a strong message to foreign investors .
