( agence france - presse , singapore , 24th ) - " international information company " published a report today , pointing out that in the next two years , the asia - pacific region will have more computer program designers and other professional research and development personnel than north america .
north america is the region with the largest concentration of research and development personnel in 2001 , and the asia - pacific region has replaced europe and has risen to the world 's second largest research and development population .
however , the " international information " report said that the strong growth of china and india is expected to push the asia - pacific region to the top in 2005 .
asia , especially india , is the main source of professionals in north america 's information industry .
" international information " said , " in the next five years , the growth of the asia - pacific region is expected to be much stronger than that of north america , especially those big countries , china and india . "
" international information " said that there were 7.8 million research and development personnel in 2001 , which is expected to increase to 13.5 million in 2006 .
the report pointed out that at the end of 2001 there were 1.7 million it research and development personnel in asia .
" international information " said that the decline in the number of information professionals in north america was partly due to the decline in the technology industry in the region .
study shows father 's genes may affect child birth time
( agence france - presse , paris , 28 th ) - according to a danish research report published in the british medical weekly , which will be published on saturday , father 's genes may affect the time of birth .
about 5% of pregnant women will have late production , that is , the time of pregnancy will reach 294 days .
at present , it is known that this problem will cause health problems to pregnant women and children , but it is still a mystery .
danish researchers followed 43,000 birth cases between 1980 and 1992 , with at least two children , and the first time they were pregnant .
at the time of analysis , they only used the data of their previous two production .
on the whole , nearly 20% of these women who have been pregnant for more than a long time have the same experience during the second pregnancy .
however , when the first and second children came from different father , the ratio dropped slightly to more than 15 percent .
" this is already a lot .
this means that if you ( the second child ) are the same partners , then you are more likely to be pregnant for a long time than those who change the partners . "
the study report said : " if women change their partners when they are pregnant every time , they can reduce the risk of repeated late production phenomena .
we believe this is a new discovery .
and this result means that the time of birth may be determined by the father 's genes . "
