shanghai port transcends kaohsiung to become world 's fourth largest container port
xinhua news agency , shanghai , january 10 ( reporter feng yizhen ) according to information from the port industry , the container throughput of shanghai port last year was 86.12 - million teus , while the container throughput of taiwan 's kaohsiung port was about 8.891 - million teus , and the shanghai port exceeded kaohsiung port and became the world 's fourth largest container port .
last year , the global economy turned warm and china 's economy continued to develop , injecting new vitality into the development of the shanghai port .
in 2001 , the shanghai port 's container handling volume reached 6.34 - million containers , which exceeded 7 - million and 8 - million teus last year , with the container handling volume reaching 86.12 - million teus , a sharp increase of 35.8 percent over the previous year , the total volume of cargo handling reached 260 - million tons , an increase of 19 percent over the previous year , and the export volume exceeded 100 - million tons for the first time , an increase of 22 percent over the previous year .
relying on the vast economic hinterland , the shanghai port has a huge network of direct flights , and has become the port with the largest number of air routes and the largest density of flights .
at present , shanghai port has flights in 12 regions in the world , and has trade ties with more than 400 ports in the world . every day , there are air routes to europe and north america , and every week there are flights to the mediterranean sea , the persian gulf , and australia .
each month , there are more than 1,300 flights to all parts of the world .
the shanghai port , which is speeding up the construction of an international shipping center , will break through 9.5 million teus this year , strive to reach 10 million teus , and achieve the original goal one year ahead of schedule .
