eu confirms huge diamond deal against anti - monopoly
xinhua news agency , brussels , january 16 ( reporter tian fan ) - the european commission announced on the 16 th that the european union has initially identified the world 's largest diamond supplier , debilis company , as well as the russian diamond company , as the contract of diamond trade worth 4 billion euros , as a violation of the european union 's anti - monopoly law .
in south africa and britain , the company , which also owns the company 's headquarters , controls 60 to 65 percent of the world 's unprocessed diamonds , while the russian diamond company is the only diamond mining company in russia , and is also the world 's second largest producer of unprocessed diamonds .
according to a five - year contract signed by the two companies , the russian diamond company has agreed to provide half of the annual diamond output , which is worth about 800 million euros , to the company , and the company will be responsible for pushing the diamonds to the market .
the european commission pointed out in a statement that the contract will restrict the free competition between russia and the world diamond market , and will enable the company to abuse its dominant position to effectively control the quantity , quality , and even price of diamonds in the world market .
according to the eu 's anti - monopoly law , the two companies can raise objections to the eu commission 's decision within two months , and the eu commission will continue its anti - monopoly investigation of the two companies .
